The probability is that the confiscation took place on the first of these occasions, in B. e. 42 or 41. At that time Tibullus, according to Dissen’s chronology, would have been 17 or 18 years of age, and therefore just liable for military service. To this date therefore he assigns the 10th Elegy of the First Book, which the poet wrote on the occasion os receiving his first summons to arms, and in which he expresses in passionate language his hatred of war and his longing for ease and peace. ln this poem there is no mention of any loss of property: so Dissen conjectures that the confiscation took place after Tibullus had started for the wars, and that he did not , return to his· reduced estate till tae. 32, when he would have completed his full period of ten years' service in the ’ cavalry.
